Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:07.000 --> 00:00:11.100
Shepherd's pie is a hearty casserole
of cooked ground meat, and vegetables.

00:00:11.100 --> 00:00:14.000
Topped with a fluffy layer of
mashed potatoes.

00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:18.000
A Great Britain comfort food,
this one dish meal it easy to prepare

00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:21.500
from ingredients you have on hand.

00:00:21.500 --> 00:00:23.800
Step One:
Make mashed potatoes.

00:00:23.800 --> 00:00:27.000
Peel and cut up several potatoes.

00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:31.000
Boil them for about 20 minutes in
salted water until tender.

00:00:31.000 --> 00:00:35.000
Mash the potatoes in a bowl with butter,
and any other seasonings you like.

00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:37.500
Step Two:
Saute the veggies.

00:00:37.500 --> 00:00:40.200
You can add any vegetable
to shepherd's pie,

00:00:40.200 --> 00:00:43.000
but, traditionally it includes
carrots and onions.

00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:47.000
Heat oil in a large frying pan,
and saute diced onions and carrots

00:00:47.000 --> 00:00:50.000
until they are cooked through.

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:52.000
Step Three:
Cook the meat.

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:54.800
Add ground meat to the sauteed
carrots and onions.

00:00:54.800 --> 00:00:59.600
Shepherd's pie is traditionally made
with lamb, but ground beef, turkey,

00:00:59.600 --> 00:01:02.000
chicken, and even fish works too.

00:01:02.000 --> 00:01:05.700
Saute the meat until it is thoroughly
brown, seasoning along the way

00:01:05.700 --> 00:01:09.500
with salt, pepper, and your
favorite herbs.

00:01:09.500 --> 00:01:13.000
For moist and flavorful meat,
add about a half cup of broth,

00:01:13.000 --> 00:01:17.000
and cook over low heat for about
10 minutes.

00:01:17.000 --> 00:01:20.100
Some recipes call for a pinch of
thickening agent, like flour,

00:01:20.100 --> 00:01:23.100
to make the meat mixture
thicker.

00:01:23.100 --> 00:01:26.000
Step Four:
Add more vegetables.

00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:29.300
For color and nutrition, sprinkle
a couple handfuls of frozen

00:01:29.300 --> 00:01:32.400
corn and peas into the meat
mixture.

00:01:32.400 --> 00:01:35.500
Step Five:
Assemble the Shepherd's Pie.

00:01:35.500 --> 00:01:38.500
Spoon the beef and vegetables
into a baking dish.

00:01:38.500 --> 00:01:42.500
Then spread the mashed
potatoes evenly across on top.

00:01:42.500 --> 00:01:46.000
Step Six:
Bake for 30 minutes.

00:01:46.000 --> 00:01:51.000
Bake the Shepherd's pie in a
400 degree oven for a half hour.

